  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health and Nutrition Response to the Horn of Africa Drought</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to reduce mortalities and morbidities related to drought and disease outbreaks among drought-affected communities of Ethiopia through the provision of life-saving and emergency health and nutrition services. UNICEF will use CERF to procure and distribute essential health and nutrition supplies including Cholera Treatment Centre kits and to functionalise Mobile Health and Nutrition Teams and Sustainable Outreach Support Teams. A total of 224,000 people including 175,680 children will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within four months.</narrative>
  </description>
